SIMPLE: hunter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hunter
<hw>Hunt"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
hunts wild animals either for sport or for food; a huntsman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dog that scents game, or is trained to the chase;
a hunting dog.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A horse used in the chase; especially, a
thoroughbred, bred and trained for hunting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who hunts or seeks after anything, as if for
game; <as>as, a fortune <ex>hunter</ex> a place
<ex>hunter</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No keener <qex>hunter</qex> after glory breathes.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind of spider. See
<cref>Hunting spider</cref>, under <er>Hunting</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A hunting watch, or one of which the crystal is
protected by a metallic cover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hunter's room</b></col>, <cd>the lunation after the
harvest moon.</cd> -- <col><b>Hunter's screw</b></col>
<fld>(Mech.)</fld>, <cd>a differential screw, so named from the
inventor. See under <er>Differential</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hunterian</ent>⟦br⟧
